T1  - The dilution impact of daily fund flows on open-end mutual funds
AU  - Greene, Jason T
AU  - Hodges, Charles W
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 65
IS  - 1
SP  - 131
EP  - 158
PY  - 2002
DA  - 2002/07/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/S0304-405X(02)00137-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304405X0200137X
KW  - Mutual funds
KW  - Flows
KW  - Daily fund flows
AB  - We examine how mutual fund flows that are correlated with subsequent fund returns can have a dilution impact on the performance of open-end funds. Active trading of open-end funds has a meaningful economic impact on the returns of passive, nontrading shareholders, particularly in U.S.-based international funds. The overall sample of domestic equity funds shows no dilution impact, but we find an annualized negative impact of 0.48% in international funds (and nearly 1% for a subsample of funds whose daily flows are particularly large). The exchange and pricing policies of mutual funds can thus have important performance-related implications.
